<div style="text-align: left; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; background: rgba(51, 51, 51,.9); padding: 10px; color:white; font-size:large">
    <p>Hello! My name is Kendrick Davis, and I am a SQL God. I know what you are thinking: "is he immortal, omniscient, and omnipotent?" Yes, yes I am; all thanks to the powers of Structured Query Language. I know it is hard to believe, but I promise that by the time you are done reading this article, you will believe that you can transcend your present reality through the powers of SQL.</p>
    <p>Let me take you on a journey through the enchanted world of SQL, where mere mortals tremble at the sight of a complex JOIN statement, and where the SELECT clause holds the keys to unlocking the mysteries of the universe (or at least your database).</p>
    <p>SQL isn't just a language; it's a way of life. Forget about mundane activities like eating and sleeping; true SQL masters thrive on crafting elegant queries and optimizing database performance. We don't dream in colors; we dream in tables, rows, and columns.</p>
    <p>Imagine a world where every problem can be solved with a perfectly crafted SQL query. Need to find your soulmate? Just INNER JOIN the tables of eligible candidates based on compatibility scores and shared interests. Want to achieve world peace? Simply UPDATE the 'conflict' table and SET status='resolved'. Easy peasy, lemon squeezy.</p>
